    "Guidelines for skin lesion imaging have been suggested to facilitate the capture of high-quality images (76, 77).",
    "These guidelines include suggestions for adequate lighting, background, field of view, image orientation, and color calibration.",
    "Additional recommendations are suggested for photographing skin of color (78).",
    "A comprehensive, multifaceted solution is necessary to enhance image quality.",
    "Educating dermatology residents in photography might contribute to improving image quality in a clinical setting (79)."
